/-- Higham, 2nd ed., Chapter 13, Section 13.2, equation (13.11a):
    combining the computed product `─ѕ = P + ╬ћC` with the computed subtraction
    `┼ю = AРѓѓРѓѓ - ─ѕ + F` gives `┼ю = AРѓѓРѓѓ - P + (F - ╬ћC)`.

    This additive form is the exact algebraic core of the displayed
    `┼ю = AРѓѓРѓѓ - L╠ѓРѓѓРѓЂ U╠ѓРѓЂРѓѓ + ╬ћS`; for the source matrices, instantiate
    `P` with `L╠ѓРѓѓРѓЂ U╠ѓРѓЂРѓѓ` and `╬ћS` with `F - ╬ћC`. -/
theorem higham13_eq13_11a_subtraction_error {╬▒ : Type*} [AddCommGroup ╬▒]
    (Shat A22 Chat F product DeltaC : ╬▒)
    (hsub : Shat = A22 - Chat + F)
    (hprod : Chat = product + DeltaC) :
    Shat = A22 - product + (F - DeltaC) := by
  rw [hsub, hprod]
  abel

/-- Higham, 2nd ed., Chapter 13, Section 13.2, equation (13.11b), scalar
    first-order norm form.

    Equation (13.10) gives the subtraction error `F`, while (13.4) gives
    `─ѕ = L╠ѓРѓѓРѓЂ U╠ѓРѓЂРѓѓ + ╬ћC`.  If `Рђќ╬ћSРђќ РЅц Рђќ╬ћCРђќ + РђќFРђќ`, `Рђќ─ѕРђќ` is bounded by the
    product term plus `Рђќ╬ћCРђќ`, and the product error is first-order, then the
    displayed `Рђќ╬ћSРђќ` bound holds with an explicit second-order witness. -/
theorem higham13_eq13_11b_trailing_schur_error_firstOrder
    (normDeltaS normDeltaC normF normA22 normChat normL21 normU12 u cРѓЂ : РёЮ)
    (hu : 0 РЅц u) (hcРѓЂ : 0 РЅц cРѓЂ)
    (_hA22 : 0 РЅц normA22) (hL21 : 0 РЅц normL21) (hU12 : 0 РЅц normU12)
    (hDeltaS : normDeltaS РЅц normDeltaC + normF)
    (hDeltaC : FirstOrderLe u (cРѓЂ * u * normL21 * normU12) normDeltaC)
    (hF : normF РЅц u * (normA22 + normChat))
    (hChat : normChat РЅц normL21 * normU12 + normDeltaC) :
    FirstOrderLe u
      (u * (normA22 + normL21 * normU12 + cРѓЂ * (normL21 * normU12)))
      normDeltaS := by
  rcases hDeltaC with РЪеK, hK, hDeltaC_boundРЪЕ
  refine РЪеK * (1 + u) + cРѓЂ * (normL21 * normU12), ?_, ?_РЪЕ
  ┬и have hu1 : 0 РЅц 1 + u := by linarith
    have hLU : 0 РЅц normL21 * normU12 := mul_nonneg hL21 hU12
    exact add_nonneg (mul_nonneg hK hu1) (mul_nonneg hcРѓЂ hLU)
  ┬и have hF_expanded :
        normF РЅц u * (normA22 + normL21 * normU12 + normDeltaC) := by
      have hinside : normA22 + normChat РЅц
          normA22 + normL21 * normU12 + normDeltaC := by
        linarith
      exact le_trans hF (mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_left hinside hu)
    have hmain :
        normDeltaS РЅц normDeltaC +
          u * (normA22 + normL21 * normU12 + normDeltaC) := by
      linarith
    nlinarith [hmain, hDeltaC_bound]

/-- Higham, 2nd ed., Chapter 13, Section 13.2, equation (13.11), assembled
    from the matrix-multiplication model (13.4) and subtraction model (13.10).

    The exact identity uses `╬ћS = F - ╬ћC`, where `╬ћC` is the product residual
    for `─ѕ = L╠ѓРѓѓРѓЂ├ЏРѓЂРѓѓ + ╬ћC` and `F` is the subtraction residual for
    `┼ю = AРѓѓРѓѓ - ─ѕ + F`.  The scalar conclusion is the first-order source bound
    for `Рђќ╬ћSРђќ`, retaining the norm aggregation assumptions explicitly. -/
theorem higham13_eq13_11_from_matmul_subtraction_specs
    {r s t : Type*} [Fintype r]
    (u cРѓЂ normA22 normChat normF normL21 normU12 normDeltaC normDeltaS : РёЮ)
    (Lhat21 : Matrix s r РёЮ) (Uhat12 : Matrix r t РёЮ)
    (A22 Chat DeltaC F Shat : Matrix s t РёЮ)
    (hu : 0 РЅц u) (hcРѓЂ : 0 РЅц cРѓЂ)
    (hA22 : 0 РЅц normA22) (hL21 : 0 РЅц normL21) (hU12 : 0 РЅц normU12)
    (hmul : MatMulFirstOrderSpec u cРѓЂ normL21 normU12 normDeltaC
      Lhat21 Uhat12 Chat DeltaC)
    (hsub : SubtractionFirstOrderSpec u normA22 normChat normF A22 Chat F Shat)
    (hDeltaS : normDeltaS РЅц normDeltaC + normF)
    (hChat : normChat РЅц normL21 * normU12 + normDeltaC) :
    Shat = A22 - Lhat21 * Uhat12 + (F - DeltaC) РѕД
      FirstOrderLe u
        (u * (normA22 + normL21 * normU12 + cРѓЂ * (normL21 * normU12)))
        normDeltaS := by
  refine РЪе?_, ?_РЪЕ
  ┬и exact higham13_eq13_11a_subtraction_error
      Shat A22 Chat F (Lhat21 * Uhat12) DeltaC hsub.equation hmul.equation
  ┬и exact higham13_eq13_11b_trailing_schur_error_firstOrder
      normDeltaS normDeltaC normF normA22 normChat normL21 normU12 u cРѓЂ
      hu hcРѓЂ hA22 hL21 hU12 hDeltaS
      (by simpa [MatMulFirstOrderBound] using hmul.norm_bound)
      hsub.norm_bound hChat

/-- Demmel--Higham--Schreiber [326], Theorem 2.1 proof boundary:
    rounded Schur-complement update, first-order scalar form.

    The recovered Pro audit of Higham Theorem 13.6 identified this as the
    first local layer needed before the recursive DHS factorization theorem:
    the product model (13.4) and subtraction model (13.10) assemble to
    `S_hat = A22 - L21_hat * U12_hat + DeltaS`, with the displayed
    first-order Schur-update bound. -/
theorem dhs_schur_update_firstOrder
    {r s t : Type*} [Fintype r]
    (u cРѓЂ normA22 normChat normF normL21 normU12 normDeltaC normDeltaS : РёЮ)
    (Lhat21 : Matrix s r РёЮ) (Uhat12 : Matrix r t РёЮ)
    (A22 Chat DeltaC F Shat : Matrix s t РёЮ)
    (hu : 0 РЅц u) (hcРѓЂ : 0 РЅц cРѓЂ)
    (hA22 : 0 РЅц normA22) (hL21 : 0 РЅц normL21) (hU12 : 0 РЅц normU12)
    (hmul : MatMulFirstOrderSpec u cРѓЂ normL21 normU12 normDeltaC
      Lhat21 Uhat12 Chat DeltaC)
    (hsub : SubtractionFirstOrderSpec u normA22 normChat normF A22 Chat F Shat)
    (hDeltaS : normDeltaS РЅц normDeltaC + normF)
    (hChat : normChat РЅц normL21 * normU12 + normDeltaC) :
    Shat = A22 - Lhat21 * Uhat12 + (F - DeltaC) РѕД
      FirstOrderLe u
        (u * (normA22 + normL21 * normU12 + cРѓЂ * (normL21 * normU12)))
        normDeltaS :=
  higham13_eq13_11_from_matmul_subtraction_specs
    u cРѓЂ normA22 normChat normF normL21 normU12 normDeltaC normDeltaS
    Lhat21 Uhat12 A22 Chat DeltaC F Shat hu hcРѓЂ hA22 hL21 hU12 hmul
    hsub hDeltaS hChat

/-- Higham, 2nd ed., Chapter 13, Section 13.2, equation (13.13), scalar
    first-order aggregation form.

    This combines the local trailing Schur perturbation `╬ћS` with an already
    expanded recursive factorization perturbation `╬ћ┼ю` to obtain the displayed
    first-order `╬ћAРѓѓРѓѓ` bound.  The theorem is deliberately scalar: the exact
    matrix identities around (13.12a) and the expansion of `Рђќ┼юРђќ` from (13.10)
    remain separate proof-step obligations. -/
theorem higham13_eq13_13_trailing_block_error_firstOrder
    (normDeltaA22 normDeltaS normDeltaShat normA22 normL21U12 normL22U22
      u cРѓЂ ╬┤ ╬И : РёЮ)
    (hDeltaA22 : normDeltaA22 РЅц normDeltaS + normDeltaShat)
    (hDeltaS : FirstOrderLe u
      (u * (normA22 + normL21U12 + cРѓЂ * normL21U12))
      normDeltaS)
    (hDeltaShat : FirstOrderLe u
      (u * (╬┤ * normA22 + ╬┤ * normL21U12 + ╬И * normL22U22))
      normDeltaShat) :
    FirstOrderLe u
      (u * ((1 + ╬┤) * normA22 + (1 + cРѓЂ + ╬┤) * normL21U12 +
        ╬И * normL22U22))
      normDeltaA22 := by
  refine (FirstOrderLe.add hDeltaS hDeltaShat hDeltaA22).mono_leading ?_
  ring_nf
  exact le_rfl

/-- Higham, 2nd ed., Chapter 13, Section 13.2, equation (13.13), exact
    additive identity behind the trailing block.

    If `┼ю = AРѓѓРѓѓ - P + ╬ћS` and the recursive factorization gives
    `Q = ┼ю + ╬ћ┼ю`, then `P + Q = AРѓѓРѓѓ + (╬ћS + ╬ћ┼ю)`.  For the source display,
    instantiate `P` with `L╠ѓРѓѓРѓЂ├ЏРѓЂРѓѓ` and `Q` with `L╠ѓРѓѓРѓѓ├ЏРѓѓРѓѓ`. -/
theorem higham13_eq13_13_trailing_block_identity {╬▒ : Type*} [AddCommGroup ╬▒]
    (product recursiveProduct Shat A22 DeltaS DeltaShat : ╬▒)
    (hShat : Shat = A22 - product + DeltaS)
    (hRecursive : recursiveProduct = Shat + DeltaShat) :
    product + recursiveProduct = A22 + (DeltaS + DeltaShat) := by
  rw [hRecursive, hShat]
  abel

/-- Higham, 2nd ed., Chapter 13, Section 13.2, equation (13.13), assembled
    from the product/subtraction specs and the recursive induction spec.

    This is the source proof step after (13.11)--(13.12): the exact trailing
    block residual follows by adding the local Schur perturbation `╬ћS = F - ╬ћC`
    to the recursive perturbation `╬ћ┼ю`, and the scalar first-order bound follows
    from the local Eq. (13.11) bound plus an explicitly expanded induction
    bound.  The hypotheses still expose the norm aggregation and `┼ю`-to-`AРѓѓРѓѓ`
    expansion assumptions, so this is not the full computed-factor theorem. -/
theorem higham13_eq13_13_from_matmul_subtraction_induction_specs
    {r s : Type*} [Fintype r] [Fintype s]
    (u cРѓЂ ╬┤ ╬И normA22 normChat normF normL21 normU12 normDeltaC normDeltaS
      normShat normLhat22 normUhat22 normL22U22 normDeltaShat normDeltaA22 : РёЮ)
    (Lhat21 : Matrix s r РёЮ) (Uhat12 : Matrix r s РёЮ)
    (A22 Chat DeltaC F Shat DeltaShat Lhat22 Uhat22 : Matrix s s РёЮ)
    (hu : 0 РЅц u) (hcРѓЂ : 0 РЅц cРѓЂ)
    (hA22 : 0 РЅц normA22) (hL21 : 0 РЅц normL21) (hU12 : 0 РЅц normU12)
    (hmul : MatMulFirstOrderSpec u cРѓЂ normL21 normU12 normDeltaC
      Lhat21 Uhat12 Chat DeltaC)
    (hsub : SubtractionFirstOrderSpec u normA22 normChat normF A22 Chat F Shat)
    (hind : PartitionedLUFirstOrderSpec u ╬┤ ╬И normShat normLhat22 normUhat22
      normDeltaShat Shat DeltaShat Lhat22 Uhat22)
    (hDeltaS : normDeltaS РЅц normDeltaC + normF)
    (hChat : normChat РЅц normL21 * normU12 + normDeltaC)
    (hDeltaA22 : normDeltaA22 РЅц normDeltaS + normDeltaShat)
    (hDeltaShat : FirstOrderLe u
      (u * (╬┤ * normA22 + ╬┤ * (normL21 * normU12) + ╬И * normL22U22))
      normDeltaShat) :
    (Lhat21 * Uhat12 + Lhat22 * Uhat22 =
      A22 + ((F - DeltaC) + DeltaShat)) РѕД
      FirstOrderLe u
        (u * ((1 + ╬┤) * normA22 + (1 + cРѓЂ + ╬┤) * (normL21 * normU12) +
          ╬И * normL22U22))
        normDeltaA22 := by
  have hEq11 :=
    higham13_eq13_11_from_matmul_subtraction_specs
      u cРѓЂ normA22 normChat normF normL21 normU12 normDeltaC normDeltaS
      Lhat21 Uhat12 A22 Chat DeltaC F Shat hu hcРѓЂ hA22 hL21 hU12 hmul
      hsub hDeltaS hChat
  refine РЪе?_, ?_РЪЕ
  ┬и exact higham13_eq13_13_trailing_block_identity
      (Lhat21 * Uhat12) (Lhat22 * Uhat22) Shat A22 (F - DeltaC) DeltaShat
      hEq11.1 hind.equation
  ┬и exact higham13_eq13_13_trailing_block_error_firstOrder
      normDeltaA22 normDeltaS normDeltaShat normA22 (normL21 * normU12)
      normL22U22 u cРѓЂ ╬┤ ╬И hDeltaA22 hEq11.2 hDeltaShat

/-- Higham, 2nd ed., Chapter 13, Section 13.2, Theorem 13.5 proof:
    exact block-matrix residual identity.

    If the four computed block residual equations hold for `(1,1)`, `(1,2)`,
    `(2,1)`, and `(2,2)`, then the assembled computed block factors satisfy
    `L╠ѓ U╠ѓ = A + ╬ћA`, with `╬ћA` assembled blockwise.  This is the exact algebraic
    bridge from equations (13.6), (13.8), (13.9), and (13.13) to the theorem's
    matrix residual statement. -/
theorem higham13_theorem13_5_block_residual_identity
    {m n ╬▒ : Type*} [Fintype m] [Fintype n] [CommRing ╬▒]
    (L11 U11 A11 DeltaA11 : Matrix m m ╬▒)
    (U12 A12 DeltaA12 : Matrix m n ╬▒)
    (L21 A21 DeltaA21 : Matrix n m ╬▒)
    (L22 U22 A22 DeltaA22 : Matrix n n ╬▒)
    (h11 : L11 * U11 = A11 + DeltaA11)
    (h12 : L11 * U12 = A12 + DeltaA12)
    (h21 : L21 * U11 = A21 + DeltaA21)
    (h22 : L21 * U12 + L22 * U22 = A22 + DeltaA22) :
    Matrix.fromBlocks L11 0 L21 L22 * Matrix.fromBlocks U11 U12 0 U22 =
      Matrix.fromBlocks A11 A12 A21 A22 +
        Matrix.fromBlocks DeltaA11 DeltaA12 DeltaA21 DeltaA22 := by
  rw [Matrix.fromBlocks_multiply]
  simp [h11, h12, h21, h22]
  ext i j
  cases i <;> cases j <;> rfl

/-- Higham, 2nd ed., Chapter 13, Section 13.2, Theorem 13.5 proof:
    exact assembled residual identity obtained directly from the source-facing
    computed-operation specs for (13.6), (13.8), and (13.9), plus the trailing
    block residual equation (13.13). -/
theorem higham13_theorem13_5_block_residual_identity_from_specs
    {r s : Type*} [Fintype r] [Fintype s]
    (u cРѓѓ cРѓЃ normLhat11 normUhat11 normDeltaA11
      normUhat12 normDeltaA12 normLhat21 normDeltaA21 : РёЮ)
    (Lhat11 Uhat11 A11 DeltaA11 : Matrix r r РёЮ)
    (Uhat12 A12 DeltaA12 : Matrix r s РёЮ)
    (Lhat21 A21 DeltaA21 : Matrix s r РёЮ)
    (Lhat22 Uhat22 A22 DeltaA22 : Matrix s s РёЮ)
    (h11 : LocalLUFirstOrderSpec u cРѓЃ normLhat11 normUhat11 normDeltaA11
      A11 DeltaA11 Lhat11 Uhat11)
    (h12 : TriangularSolveFirstOrderSpec u cРѓѓ normLhat11 normUhat12 normDeltaA12
      Lhat11 A12 DeltaA12 Uhat12)
    (h21 : RightTriangularSolveFirstOrderSpec u cРѓѓ normUhat11 normLhat21 normDeltaA21
      Uhat11 A21 DeltaA21 Lhat21)
    (h22 : Lhat21 * Uhat12 + Lhat22 * Uhat22 = A22 + DeltaA22) :
    Matrix.fromBlocks Lhat11 0 Lhat21 Lhat22 *
        Matrix.fromBlocks Uhat11 Uhat12 0 Uhat22 =
      Matrix.fromBlocks A11 A12 A21 A22 +
        Matrix.fromBlocks DeltaA11 DeltaA12 DeltaA21 DeltaA22 := by
  exact higham13_theorem13_5_block_residual_identity
    Lhat11 Uhat11 A11 DeltaA11 Uhat12 A12 DeltaA12 Lhat21 A21 DeltaA21
    Lhat22 Uhat22 A22 DeltaA22 h11.equation h12.equation h21.equation h22

